title: Definitions
context: §200D-1 Definitions. As used in this chapter, unless the context clearly requires otherwise: &ldquo;Council&rdquo; means the Kaneohe Bay regional council. &ldquo;Lead agency&rdquo; means the department of land and natural resources. &ldquo;Master plan&rdquo; means the Kaneohe Bay master plan developed pursuant to Act 208, Session Laws of Hawaii 1990, and amended by section 200D-3. &ldquo;Members&rdquo; means the members of the Kaneohe Bay regional council. [L 1993, c 317, pt of §2, §7; am L 1998, c 4, §3 and c 129, §3; am L 2009, c 68, §1; am L 2010, c 19, §4]
